    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, TILT - 9600, 9700, 9800 - REMOVE - STEERING COLUMN
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="5">
        <title>STEERING COLUMN</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the steering housing cover retaining screws and washers, and remove the housing cover
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0501007">Figure 7</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0501007" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0501007" filename="../figg05/G0501007.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 6. Steering Column Housing Cover Removal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. HOUSING COVER</callout1>
                <callout1>2. STEERING COLUMN SHAFT</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the housing removed, the turn signal harness, horn wire and trailer brake air hose
                locations are accessible (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0501008">Figure 8</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0501008" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0501008" filename="../figg05/G0501008.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 7. Steering Column Housing Cover Removed</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. HARNESS CONNECTOR</callout1>
                <callout1>2. TILT CONTROL LEVER</callout1>
                <callout1>3. TURN SIGNAL HARNESS</callout1>
                <callout1>4. HORN WIRE CONNECTOR</callout1>
                <callout1>5. HAZARD WARNING SWITCH</callout1>
                <callout1>6. TURN SIGNAL LEVER</callout1>
                <callout1>7. AIR HOSES</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the turn signal harness at the connector (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0501008">Figure 8, Item 3</hotlnk>). Disconnect the horn wire connector (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0501008">Figure 8, Item 4</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the air hoses from the trailer brake valve (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0501009">Figure 9</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0501009" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0501009" filename="../figg05/G0501009.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 8. Disconnecting Trailer Brake Valve Hoses</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the four (4) housing retaining bolts on the tilt column (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0501010">Figure 10</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0501010" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0501010" filename="../figg05/G0501010.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 9. Steering Housing Retaining Bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the or mat rolled back, remove the steering column assembly bracket from the cab floor
                by removing four bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0501011">Figure 11</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0501011" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0501011" filename="../figg05/G0501011.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 10. Steering Column Assembly Bracket Removal</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the steering column U-joint at the steering gear.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the steering column with the shaft and slip yoke.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
